<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9610] Should not throw illegal state exception during task revocation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9610</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In handleRevocation call, the remaining partitions could cause an illegal state exception on task revocation. This should also be fixed as it is expected when the tasks are cleared from the assignor onAssignment callback.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
